15/12/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister designate Ivo Sanader sent congratulations to US President George W. Bush on Sunday (14 December) for the arrest of former Iraqi President Saddam Hussein. In his letter, Sanader wrote that the capture would have a huge positive effect on the future of Iraq and the Middle East. He added that Croatia's new government would promote close relations with Washington and take an active part in international anti-terrorism efforts.
In other news, Croatian President Stipe Mesic is in Moscow, where he will meet Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin for the second time this year. Croatia's state news agency HINA quoted Croatian diplomats saying that the visit confirmed Mesic's role in maintaining political stability in the region. (Vjesnik - 15/12/03; HINA, HRT - 14/12/03)
